1
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:20,940
=About Love=

2
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 17=

3
00:01:26,860 --> 00:01:29,420
(Wild & Proud Rose)
(Women's Club)

4
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:44,920
Hi, Xiaoxi.

5
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,000
Have a seat.

6
00:01:51,790 --> 00:01:53,350
How are things with Mu?

7
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,590
I came to tell you this.

8
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:59,070
Lin Chen is only curious about my past.

9
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:01,510
Weren't you two supposed to try for a week?

10
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,120
It's only been four days.

11
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,840
I can tell

12
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,640
he's not into me.

13
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:09,190
This is just a waste of time.

14
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:13,310
Besides, I agreed to help Mu

15
00:02:13,310 --> 00:02:14,520
because of her feelings for Lin Chen.

16
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:16,680
But what if

17
00:02:17,150 --> 00:02:18,590
Lin Chen really is a good guy

18
00:02:18,590 --> 00:02:19,560
and has been loyal all along?

19
00:02:19,910 --> 00:02:20,910
How will he feel

20
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:22,680
when he finds out
that we've been deceiving him?

21
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,280
How is Mu supposed to face him?

22
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:27,630
Are you backing out

23
00:02:27,910 --> 00:02:29,150
because you have a boyfriend?

24
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,870
Has it ever occurred to you?

25
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:34,240
If it weren't for all this testing,

26
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,080
would you have trusted him?

27
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:43,080
I don't want to be Chen Qing anymore.

28
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:45,960
If you still can't trust Liu Chen,

29
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,360
find someone else.

30
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:53,430
Go see him one last time.

31
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,470
I'll consider it as the last thing

32
00:02:57,190 --> 00:02:59,120
I can do for my sister, who might not

33
00:02:59,470 --> 00:03:00,520
have much time left.

34
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:09,750
Guan,

35
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,630
your place looks nice.

36
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:13,800
You're always welcome here.

37
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,710
Where's what I asked for?

38
00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:45,900
(100 Little Things About Love)

39
00:03:45,910 --> 00:03:46,750
Zhen.

40
00:03:47,150 --> 00:03:47,990
Yes?

41
00:03:49,150 --> 00:03:50,030
Can I ask you

42
00:03:50,910 --> 00:03:52,080
where did you

43
00:03:52,470 --> 00:03:53,400
get that money?

44
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,590
I borrowed it.

45
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,030
I told you before.

46
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:00,360
From whom?

47
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,240
My parents.

48
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,400
What's wrong?

49
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,680
Why that face?

50
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,030
You're creeping me out.

51
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,040
Where were you last weekend?

52
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:21,950
I went home.

53
00:04:22,430 --> 00:04:23,360
I told you.

54
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:30,360
Stop lying to me.

55
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:34,950
Didn't you go away for the weekend

56
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,390
with that admirer of yours?

57
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,480
Who told you that?

58
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:48,880
Am I right?

59
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,640
Yes,

60
00:04:55,950 --> 00:04:57,430
but I did it for Zhen Guan.

61
00:04:57,750 --> 00:04:58,830
Otherwise, how would we

62
00:04:58,830 --> 00:05:00,310
cover the loss from the goods?

63
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:02,630
And

64
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,510
he's not an admirer.

65
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,830
He's just a friend.

66
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:06,830
Don't you know he likes you?

67
00:05:07,050 --> 00:05:07,920
That guy knows

68
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,070
you have a boyfriend,

69
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:10,630
and he still keeps hanging around you.

70
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,920
I told you to stay away from him.

71
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:15,630
I kept my distance.

72
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,950
I said no.

73
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,360
Does it make him unforgivable

74
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,800
just because he used to like me?

75
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:24,360
We're in trouble right now.

76
00:05:24,870 --> 00:05:25,800
He helped us.

77
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,070
I don't need that! How could I need that?

78
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,390
My girlfriend went on a trip
with another guy for money

79
00:05:32,830 --> 00:05:34,070
and stayed overnight with him.

80
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,310
How do you expect me to feel?

81
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,190
So, what kind of person

82
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,040
do you think I am?

83
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,870
Nothing happened between us.

84
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:43,600
Can you trust me, please?

85
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,270
Lin isn't a bad guy.

86
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:46,480
He just has a terrible sense

87
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:47,870
of humor and a sharp tongue.

88
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:50,000
Don't fall for his tricks, okay?

89
00:05:54,510 --> 00:05:55,350
Alright.

90
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,080
I trust you.

91
00:05:59,270 --> 00:06:00,160
Let's not talk about him.

92
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:02,270
Listen to me.

93
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,390
Give him his money back.

94
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:05,800
We don't need it.

95
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:07,800
Okay?

96
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:09,750
If we give it back,

97
00:06:10,430 --> 00:06:11,560
what about the money we need?

98
00:06:11,870 --> 00:06:13,190
I'll figure something out.

99
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,430
Let's not rely on his money, okay?

100
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:18,000
We're just using it to get through this.

101
00:06:18,310 --> 00:06:20,000
Once Zhen Guan gets back on track,

102
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,750
we'll pay him back.

103
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:23,950
There's nothing shameful about that.

104
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:25,920
It's not about shame.

105
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:28,000
We can sell the inventory, and...

106
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,360
And we can start fresh.

107
00:06:32,310 --> 00:06:33,150
Trust me on this.

108
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:35,830
Right now, give him

109
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:37,510
the money back.

110
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:38,920
I don't need his money.

111
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,390
You still don't trust me, do you?

112
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:48,560
How dirty do you think this money is?

113
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:53,590
Fine,

114
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,310
so you don't want it.

115
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,630
You're high and mighty.

116
00:06:57,950 --> 00:06:58,790
You're so noble.

117
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,000
I'm the cheap one.

118
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,310
Then go be noble on your own.

119
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:35,020
(100 Little Things About Love)

120
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:51,620
(An Miu)

121
00:07:58,950 --> 00:07:59,790
Hello?

122
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,510
About that thing...

123
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,040
I don't want to do it anymore.

124
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:09,480
I'm sorry.

125
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:11,880
I just don't think

126
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,390
it means anything anymore.

127
00:08:42,550 --> 00:08:43,440
Gosh!

128
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,360
I can't believe this.

129
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,630
Where are you?

130
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:52,080
Sweetie?

131
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,840
Oh, there you are!

132
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:57,120
Were you lonely at home by yourself?

133
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,840
Look at this mess!

134
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:01,270
I knew he must've torn the place apart.

135
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:04,030
We can't leave him alone at home.

136
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,960
Maybe we should send him to a pet shop.

137
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,870
You trust someone else with this?

138
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:12,270
Keeping him in a cage will make him depressed.

139
00:09:12,270 --> 00:09:13,600
Is that right?

140
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:14,630
What do you mean?

141
00:09:14,630 --> 00:09:16,200
So, we won't travel far anymore?

142
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,080
Since we chose to keep him,

143
00:09:18,270 --> 00:09:20,510
we have to give up some time and freedom.

144
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:24,390
Stop it. The cleaning lady
is coming this afternoon.

145
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:28,240
We haven't named him yet, have we?

146
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:31,630
What should we call him?

147
00:09:32,630 --> 00:09:34,030
How about...

148
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,440
"Thanks"?

149
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:39,840
"Thanks"?

150
00:09:40,670 --> 00:09:42,960
Seeing him makes all our worries disappear.

151
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:46,080
We should thank him, right?

152
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,720
And we rarely say "thanks" in daily life,

153
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:49,720
but now we can call him.

154
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,680
Mm.

155
00:09:52,390 --> 00:09:54,240
"Thanks" sounds nice.

156
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:58,120
You have a name! You're Thanks!

157
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,390
Thanks.

158
00:10:02,290 --> 00:10:03,150
Thanks.

159
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:04,080
Honey,

160
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,320
thanks.

161
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,550
Honey, thank...

162
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:14,940
(Mom)

163
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,390
Hello, Mom.

164
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:25,320
You're coming over now?

165
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:28,320
No, we've got everything we need here.

166
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,870
Xiu and I have plans this afternoon.

167
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:33,910
Buying a new car.

168
00:10:34,390 --> 00:10:37,120
Didn't you say we should
get a better one to look good?

169
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:39,720
I know, I know.

170
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,080
It's definitely time for an upgrade.

171
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:45,080
No,

172
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:46,750
Xiu earned the money,

173
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,790
from songwriting.

174
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:52,120
Why would I lie to you?

175
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,670
Alright, you can come with us.

176
00:10:58,030 --> 00:10:59,390
Okay, we'll pick you up.

177
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,550
Alright, bye.

178
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:06,790
Mom said she wants to come with us.

179
00:11:07,030 --> 00:11:07,870
Okay.

180
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:10,080
I'll work harder from now on

181
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,600
and get us a big house

182
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,790
with a yard.

183
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:14,960
Why?

184
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,120
Buying a wedding home for Thanks?

185
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:17,960
No,

186
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,000
to give him

187
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,270
more space to move around.

188
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:21,670
So later, when we travel,

189
00:11:21,670 --> 00:11:23,670
we can leave him home and let him go wild.

190
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:26,360
But mainly because

191
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,550
you like growing flowers.

192
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,440
This yard is huge.

193
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:32,150
I want to grow lots of flowers too.

194
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:34,750
Then our future houses must all have yards.

195
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:36,150
That would cost a fortune.

196
00:11:36,750 --> 00:11:39,270
We can just stay here
a couple of days each year.

197
00:11:39,270 --> 00:11:40,360
You don't think I can do it?

198
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:42,320
Once my songs start streaming big,

199
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,390
the money will soar.

200
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:45,030
I'll buy this place outright.

201
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,000
If you get rich, will you still want me?

202
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:48,440
If you want me, I'm yours.

203
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,080
That's way too expensive.

204
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:55,120
Let's treat it as a dream.

205
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:00,000
It'll come true.

206
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,240
Better to be realistic.

207
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:05,790
Getting a new car is good enough.

208
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:07,790
Have you picked a model?

209
00:12:09,550 --> 00:12:10,910
I don't know much about cars.

210
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,960
There aren't many
good all-round cars, are there?

211
00:12:14,670 --> 00:12:16,270
Then let Mom help us.

212
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,480
So, tonight,

213
00:12:21,670 --> 00:12:23,080
let's have dinner with Mom.

214
00:12:24,670 --> 00:12:25,630
Tonight?

215
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,960
It might not work.

216
00:12:28,390 --> 00:12:29,240
I promised someone

217
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:30,840
I'd help fix a demo tonight.

218
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,150
I need to work on it.

219
00:12:37,550 --> 00:12:38,390
They'll pay me.

220
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:42,600
Since you promised, do it well.

221
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:46,600
Try to come home early tonight.

222
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:47,870
Okay,

223
00:12:48,030 --> 00:12:48,910
I'll be home as I'm done.

224
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:52,120
Thanks.

225
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,040
Hi there!

226
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,790
Why are you so late?

227
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:05,080
What's up?

228
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:07,670
I've got something serious to tell you.

229
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:09,480
I've got something serious too.

230
00:13:09,890 --> 00:13:10,750
How serious?

231
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:11,600
Very.

232
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,260
- You go first.
- Okay.

233
00:13:15,150 --> 00:13:16,550
I went to his place last night.

234
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:18,550
We had some wine.

235
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,510
I wanted some Baijiu, though.

236
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:21,990
Never mind.

237
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:23,910
I can fake being tipsy, you know.

238
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:25,910
Then we chatted a bit.

239
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,750
I don't even remember exactly what.

240
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,040
Get to the point.

241
00:13:30,630 --> 00:13:31,470
The point?

242
00:13:32,390 --> 00:13:35,120
Well, his ex girlfriend posted

243
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,480
a photo.

244
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:37,510
It didn't register with me.

245
00:13:37,510 --> 00:13:39,270
But yesterday, I realized it's his bedroom.

246
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:41,390
You're following his ex?

247
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:45,080
It could be an old photo.

248
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:47,110
Maybe she posted it
to give you the wrong idea.

249
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,000
No way.

250
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,080
When I zoomed in,

251
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,480
I saw a magazine on the table.

252
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,790
It was published this month.

253
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,510
I saw it last night.

254
00:13:54,510 --> 00:13:55,350
Maybe it's edited.

255
00:13:56,670 --> 00:13:58,200
I mean, that's possible.

256
00:13:58,390 --> 00:14:00,670
Or maybe it's simpler than that.

257
00:14:00,870 --> 00:14:02,120
She went to his place,

258
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:03,790
and they got back together.

259
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:04,910
After all, that girl

260
00:14:04,910 --> 00:14:06,200
hasn't moved on.

261
00:14:08,670 --> 00:14:09,630
Did you ask him about it?

262
00:14:09,870 --> 00:14:10,750
No.

263
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:12,960
The vibe wasn't right.

264
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:14,510
I thought I'd ask later.

265
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:16,750
Does he not even know his ex has been

266
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:17,630
harassing you?

267
00:14:17,630 --> 00:14:20,030
He told me he cut her off completely.

268
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,600
I swear, I almost wanted to

269
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:25,030
go confront her and dig
everything up right now.

270
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:26,600
What's the point?

271
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:29,000
What would you even dig up

272
00:14:31,030 --> 00:14:32,360
with his ex?

273
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:38,960
Stop staring at me.

274
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:42,120
When did you get here?

275
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:43,550
I've been here for a while.

276
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,750
Am I wrong or not?

277
00:14:49,150 --> 00:14:51,030
Exes never say anything nice.

278
00:14:51,550 --> 00:14:52,870
So why bother believing them?

279
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,080
If you love him,

280
00:14:54,550 --> 00:14:55,670
he's the best for you.

281
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:57,360
If not, just break up.

282
00:14:57,550 --> 00:14:58,750
Don't overthink it.

283
00:14:58,750 --> 00:14:59,790
Who are you?

284
00:14:59,790 --> 00:15:01,320
It's none of your business.

285
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:02,750
Is it fun eavesdropping?

286
00:15:02,910 --> 00:15:04,720
Just giving a friendly reminder.

287
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,840
You've been gossiping nonstop here.

288
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:09,150
It's messing up my
foreign language practice, big sister.

289
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:11,750
Big sister?

290
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,720
I'm not your sister, old man.

291
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:20,120
Can you be a little gentler,

292
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:21,160
ma'am?

293
00:15:21,910 --> 00:15:22,910
Ma'am?

294
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:25,630
Fine, one of us is dying today!

295
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,550
Wait, miss!

296
00:15:29,910 --> 00:15:31,270
Please watch your manners, lady.

297
00:15:31,790 --> 00:15:33,000
Open your eyes. Look at me.

298
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,080
How old do you think I am?

299
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,720
Thirty-six.

300
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,200
Thirty-six?

301
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:39,670
Sixteen, sixteen, sixteen!

302
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,480
Eight years old!

303
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:42,630
Eight it is, okay?

304
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,120
He's Gong, right?

305
00:15:44,390 --> 00:15:45,230
Yeah.

306
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:46,720
You said I'm like him?

307
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:47,560
No way!

308
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,360
I meant...

309
00:15:50,790 --> 00:15:51,630
your hairstyle.

310
00:15:51,870 --> 00:15:52,710
Fine.

311
00:15:53,270 --> 00:15:54,720
Maybe I should reflect on myself.

312
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:56,790
What terrible thing

313
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:58,630
did I ever do

314
00:15:58,630 --> 00:16:00,670
to make you think I'm like him?

315
00:16:00,670 --> 00:16:01,720
So, this is how you've

316
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:02,910
seen me all these years?

317
00:16:03,910 --> 00:16:04,750
No.

318
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:05,960
Miss Cherry,

319
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:07,550
I was a bit presumptuous.

320
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:09,550
Let me apologize with coffee instead of wine.

321
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:10,390
Put it down!

322
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,550
Jiang Yifan,

323
00:16:13,550 --> 00:16:15,790
you said you had something serious to tell me.

324
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,030
If it's really serious,

325
00:16:18,630 --> 00:16:20,440
maybe Miss Cherry should excuse herself?

326
00:16:24,790 --> 00:16:27,480
Actually, it's nothing that serious.

327
00:16:28,270 --> 00:16:29,600
I called you both here today

328
00:16:29,870 --> 00:16:31,120
just to let you know

329
00:16:32,270 --> 00:16:33,750
I've come clean to Bei.

330
00:16:34,630 --> 00:16:36,200
I told him everything.

331
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:43,320
By "everything",

332
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,000
does that mean...

333
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:46,150
I suppose...

334
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:47,870
Not my part, right?

335
00:16:52,150 --> 00:16:53,670
How could you two not be part of it?

336
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:00,030
I've told him the whole true story.

337
00:17:01,790 --> 00:17:02,790
Bei said, after the play,

338
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:04,750
we should grab late-night snacks together.

339
00:17:10,270 --> 00:17:11,510
After the play,

340
00:17:12,350 --> 00:17:13,350
let's have dinner.

341
00:17:14,830 --> 00:17:15,670
Don't leave.

342
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:20,880
Look at you two.

343
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,270
Are you falling for each other?

344
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,590
Problem solved perfectly!

345
00:17:25,030 --> 00:17:26,200
Why aren't you happy?

346
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,590
We're happy.

347
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,480
Very happy, right?

348
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,000
Right, right.

349
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:36,640
Totally happy.

350
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:40,030
But no need for dinner, really.

351
00:17:40,270 --> 00:17:41,200
Exactly.

352
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,040
We're family...

353
00:17:43,070 --> 00:17:45,270
We're not even close. No need.

354
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:47,310
You two just live your lives peacefully.

355
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:49,400
Forget all those past grudges.

356
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:50,920
Let them go!

357
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:51,760
Let them go.

358
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:57,480
You two are so alike.

359
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:00,830
Yingtao,

360
00:18:00,830 --> 00:18:02,750
I was going to take you to a play today,

361
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:04,110
but I didn't get front-row seats.

362
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:05,270
It's over your head anyway.

363
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:06,820
Let's just grab late-night snacks.

364
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:07,910
It's settled.

365
00:18:07,910 --> 00:18:08,500
(Scoundrel Squad)

366
00:18:10,270 --> 00:18:11,440
(Tonight,)

367
00:18:12,350 --> 00:18:13,590
(don't leave)

368
00:18:17,030 --> 00:18:17,870
(after the play.)

369
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:26,920
What's wrong?

370
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:27,760
Are you okay?

371
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,520
Did I...

372
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,350
Did I pinch him too hard?

373
00:18:33,310 --> 00:18:34,160
Did I make him cry?

374
00:18:36,270 --> 00:18:37,200
Ma'am,

375
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,200
any preferences?

376
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,160
I can recommend a few.

377
00:18:39,550 --> 00:18:41,030
Also, we can

378
00:18:41,030 --> 00:18:42,640
arrange a test drive for you.

379
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,590
So, ma'am,

380
00:18:45,590 --> 00:18:46,830
would you prefer a sedan

381
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,030
or an SUV?

382
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:52,900
(You received a message on WeChat)

383
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:54,620
(Yu)

384
00:18:54,620 --> 00:18:56,820
(Got held up at the studio.
Can't make it. You guys go ahead.)

385
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,320
Mom,

386
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:00,400
Yu can't make it here.

387
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:01,270
Let's take a look first.

388
00:19:06,540 --> 00:19:07,400
This one, sir.

389
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:09,480
The latest 6 Series, a four-door coupe.

390
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:12,830
And here's the newest BMW 7 Series.

391
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:15,510
The latest BMW coupe.

392
00:19:15,510 --> 00:19:16,920
Yu, what's going on?

393
00:19:17,310 --> 00:19:19,440
Didn't we agree to come together?

394
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:21,830
Mom, we've got a problem at the studio.

395
00:19:21,830 --> 00:19:23,240
My model canceled last minute.

396
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:25,510
Are you buying the car or not?

397
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:27,200
Xiu can't make the decision.

398
00:19:28,550 --> 00:19:29,400
You decide.

399
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,920
Just pick whichever you like.

400
00:19:31,350 --> 00:19:32,400
I've got to go.

401
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:33,680
Need to make some calls.

402
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:36,950
Hello?

403
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:42,000
- Let's keep watching, young man.
- Sure.

404
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,550
Ma'am,

405
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:45,400
over here, please.

406
00:19:51,830 --> 00:19:52,670
Mom,

407
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,240
have some tea.

408
00:19:55,030 --> 00:19:55,870
Oh.

409
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:57,790
You're not working today?

410
00:19:58,070 --> 00:19:59,750
I usually work from home.

411
00:20:02,790 --> 00:20:04,070
Yu's been pretty busy.

412
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,960
Yes, she works late every day.

413
00:20:06,110 --> 00:20:06,950
It's exhausting.

414
00:20:09,310 --> 00:20:12,110
It's good for young people to earn more money,

415
00:20:12,590 --> 00:20:13,640
especially for men.

416
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:14,790
They should support the family.

417
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,160
Let's get down to business.

418
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,640
Yu's father wonders if you're okay

419
00:20:24,240 --> 00:20:25,640
with your future kids

420
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:27,920
taking Yu's last name.

421
00:20:29,310 --> 00:20:30,160
What do you think?

422
00:20:34,310 --> 00:20:35,310
Why is that?

423
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:38,270
It doesn't matter whose surname
the kids take now.

424
00:20:39,070 --> 00:20:42,440
Look at the grandson of Yu's third aunt.

425
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:44,160
He took his mom's last name.

426
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,680
But his parents divorced.

427
00:20:51,510 --> 00:20:52,350
Tell me,

428
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:56,480
who paid for this apartment

429
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:58,200
down payment?

430
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,640
You and Dad did.

431
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:04,920
But we agreed it was a loan.

432
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:07,480
We'll pay you back with interest.

433
00:21:09,030 --> 00:21:09,870
Pay back?

434
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:12,960
You mean my daughter should pay us back

435
00:21:13,310 --> 00:21:14,510
with her own money?

436
00:21:14,830 --> 00:21:16,350
What a scheme.

437
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:17,510
Mom, that's not what I mean.

438
00:21:17,510 --> 00:21:18,920
I meant we'd pay it back together.

439
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:20,070
How much do you make a month?

440
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,880
After the mortgage and daily expenses,

441
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,070
how much is left to pay us back?

442
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:27,000
I'll keep working hard.

443
00:21:28,030 --> 00:21:29,240
As parents, we both

444
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:31,480
want our daughter to live well.

445
00:21:33,070 --> 00:21:34,270
I mean,

446
00:21:35,590 --> 00:21:37,000
you don't need to pay us.

447
00:21:37,590 --> 00:21:39,270
The kids will take our family name.

448
00:21:40,070 --> 00:21:41,070
We'll raise them.

449
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:43,830
You can keep your earnings.

450
00:21:44,270 --> 00:21:46,590
No matter the surname,

451
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:48,830
they're your flesh and blood.

452
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:52,030
Honestly, we're making the bigger sacrifice.

453
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:54,030
We just want to

454
00:21:54,030 --> 00:21:55,030
lighten your burden.

455
00:21:55,350 --> 00:21:56,440
Mom, you didn't

456
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:58,920
mention this when we got married.

457
00:21:59,590 --> 00:22:01,310
If you'd known, you wouldn't have married Yu?

458
00:22:01,310 --> 00:22:02,440
No, that's not...

459
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:07,480
I didn't agree to Yu
marrying you in the first place.

460
00:22:08,310 --> 00:22:09,480
Yu has always been

461
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:12,830
strong and outstanding since childhood.

462
00:22:12,830 --> 00:22:14,240
She never gave us any trouble,

463
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:15,510
until she met you.

464
00:22:16,270 --> 00:22:18,310
I think she must've lost her mind.

465
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:19,560
For you, she even

466
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,030
lied to me and her dad.

467
00:22:21,790 --> 00:22:23,790
Your parents don't even have savings.

468
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:25,480
You can barely support yourselves.

469
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:26,640
When you got married,

470
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:28,510
you couldn't even afford a ring!

471
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,240
Paying us back?

472
00:22:31,030 --> 00:22:32,510
When will you ever repay it?

473
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:36,110
If Yu hadn't been fooled by you

474
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,720
and insisted on marrying you,

475
00:22:39,110 --> 00:22:40,440
when you're in your forties,

476
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:44,270
you'd still be trash who can't get a wife.

477
00:22:52,110 --> 00:22:53,200
The back of this car

478
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:54,680
is quite not spacious.

479
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,110
Once you have a kid,

480
00:22:56,110 --> 00:22:57,720
it'll feel way too cramped.

481
00:22:58,960 --> 00:22:59,800
Ma'am,

482
00:23:00,030 --> 00:23:01,960
this car has enough space.

483
00:23:02,550 --> 00:23:04,590
Bigger isn't always better.

484
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:05,790
This model

485
00:23:05,790 --> 00:23:07,680
is perfect for families with kids.

486
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:08,750
Look,

487
00:23:08,750 --> 00:23:10,310
windows and the sunroof

488
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:11,830
have anti-pinch sensors,

489
00:23:12,070 --> 00:23:13,480
very sensitive.

490
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:15,640
Little hands won't get caught.

491
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:17,960
And the trunk is spacious,

492
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,480
very convenient

493
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:20,480
for trips with kids.

494
00:23:22,540 --> 00:23:23,400
Ma'am,

495
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:25,110
if this one feels small,

496
00:23:25,110 --> 00:23:26,070
we have a bigger model,

497
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:27,400
plenty of room for

498
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:28,590
your future grandkids.

499
00:23:28,790 --> 00:23:30,000
Shall I show you that one?

500
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:32,760
Mom,

501
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,790
Yu and I don't want kids yet.

502
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:36,200
Our careers just started.

503
00:23:36,350 --> 00:23:38,110
We'll think about it a few years later.

504
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:39,830
You say that every year.

505
00:23:40,790 --> 00:23:42,510
Can you keep putting this off forever?

506
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,720
Honestly, Yu and I have talked about it,

507
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:46,750
and we got a puppy now.

508
00:23:47,110 --> 00:23:47,950
What?

509
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:50,480
Yu didn't tell me this.

510
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:52,510
You've got the energy for a dog,

511
00:23:52,510 --> 00:23:54,750
but not for a kid? Get a life!

512
00:23:55,030 --> 00:23:55,870
You know what?

513
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,720
Dogs are dirty.

514
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:00,790
If Yu gets pregnant, she can't be around one.

515
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:02,200
It's fine, Mom. Don't worry.

516
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:03,830
Dogs get all their vaccines now.

517
00:24:03,830 --> 00:24:04,960
I hate your excuses!

518
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:10,550
I'm seeing a play with friends tonight.

519
00:24:10,830 --> 00:24:12,510
Then we're grabbing late-night snacks.

520
00:24:12,510 --> 00:24:14,130
- I won't see you.
- That's what I told Bei.

521
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:16,400
If you two talk about it later,

522
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:17,240
don't slip up.

523
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:18,110
Got it.

524
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:19,680
I'm sorry for

525
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,200
asking you to keep this from Bei.

526
00:24:25,750 --> 00:24:27,400
I just couldn't tell him.

527
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:29,790
Never mind, anyway.

528
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:31,960
I was going to keep my mouth shut.

529
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:33,270
What difference does it make?

530
00:24:34,750 --> 00:24:36,070
Since we can't be a couple,

531
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:38,200
I might as well be

532
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:39,590
the ex who leaves

533
00:24:39,590 --> 00:24:41,680
no bad mark on your life.

534
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:45,000
Though I'm not really your ex.

535
00:24:48,270 --> 00:24:49,160
Jiang Yifan,

536
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:52,310
can I ask you one last favor?

537
00:24:52,830 --> 00:24:53,670
Of course,

538
00:24:54,270 --> 00:24:55,480
anything I can do to help.

539
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:57,070
You definitely can.

540
00:24:57,070 --> 00:24:58,030
When you see Bei later,

541
00:24:58,030 --> 00:24:59,400
check his bag and his car.

542
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:00,270
See if there's a hammer

543
00:25:00,270 --> 00:25:01,310
a wrench or something.

544
00:25:01,310 --> 00:25:02,270
Make sure they're hidden.

545
00:25:02,270 --> 00:25:03,830
I don't want to make the headlines.

546
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:05,550
You're insane.

547
00:25:07,750 --> 00:25:09,030
Oh dear.

548
00:25:09,590 --> 00:25:11,200
Tonight is

549
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:12,480
going to be interesting.

550
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:14,960
Why?

551
00:25:16,310 --> 00:25:17,510
The play.

552
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:19,200
Love story, perfect for couples.

553
00:25:20,110 --> 00:25:21,000
But you'll stop

554
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:22,240
believing in love after.

555
00:25:22,510 --> 00:25:23,510
Do you know the plot?

556
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:24,750
I've read the script.

557
00:25:25,350 --> 00:25:26,960
It's so...

558
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:29,200
How should I put it?

559
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:30,590
It's something...

560
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:36,240
Yu should never see it.

561
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,920
It'll crush her.

562
00:25:38,190 --> 00:25:39,030
Why?

563
00:25:39,030 --> 00:25:40,350
You'll see.

564
00:25:40,350 --> 00:25:41,440
But it doesn't matter.

565
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:43,400
Xiu's going to get back with Yu anyway.

566
00:25:45,790 --> 00:25:46,720
What permit does he have?

567
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:49,590
Dreams don't require a permit.

568
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:51,640
Even the worst person wants a better life.

569
00:25:51,790 --> 00:25:52,680
And,

570
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:54,920
how do you know the current Xiu

571
00:25:55,310 --> 00:25:56,510
isn't Yu's ideal type?

572
00:25:56,830 --> 00:25:57,830
Looks like you and Bei

573
00:25:57,830 --> 00:25:59,680
both hope Yu forgives her cheating husband

574
00:26:00,030 --> 00:26:01,480
like nothing happened and gets back

575
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:02,590
together with him.

576
00:26:03,270 --> 00:26:06,310
Outsiders talk about morals and rules.

577
00:26:06,310 --> 00:26:07,400
But the people involved

578
00:26:07,790 --> 00:26:09,750
care about feelings and interest.

579
00:26:09,750 --> 00:26:11,020
Am I right, Jiang Yifan?

580
00:26:11,020 --> 00:26:12,020
(Yu)

581
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,040
Hello?

582
00:26:15,350 --> 00:26:17,880
Xiaoxi, you're the only one
who can help me with this.

583
00:26:19,350 --> 00:26:20,190
You see?

584
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:22,750
(Moshi Fashion Studio)
Those seasonal pieces were made for you.

585
00:26:22,750 --> 00:26:24,480
No one else could pull off this vibe.

586
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:26,000
Oh wow.

587
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:26,960
What about this one?

588
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,400
I honestly didn't expect

589
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,240
you called me here

590
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:31,160
just for this.

591
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:33,310
Of course. Who else could I ask?

592
00:26:39,270 --> 00:26:40,310
I got

593
00:26:40,590 --> 00:26:41,480
what you wanted.

594
00:26:45,590 --> 00:26:46,430
Jiayin,

595
00:26:46,830 --> 00:26:47,960
take everyone out for lunch.

596
00:26:48,110 --> 00:26:49,280
- Okay.
- Mm.

597
00:26:50,070 --> 00:26:51,200
Come on, let's grab a bite!

598
00:26:51,830 --> 00:26:52,670
Let's go.

599
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,350
I can't give you the photo now.

600
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:04,510
I'm afraid it wasn't their fault.

601
00:27:04,510 --> 00:27:05,400
It was mine.

602
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:08,280
I get it.

603
00:27:09,070 --> 00:27:09,920
You think

604
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,750
you caused our divorce.

605
00:27:12,750 --> 00:27:13,680
You feel guilty.

606
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:15,590
I wouldn't have before.

607
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,720
But Xiu is Bei's good friend.

608
00:27:19,750 --> 00:27:21,510
Bei doesn't want his friend to split.

609
00:27:22,270 --> 00:27:23,510
He hopes you'll reconcile.

610
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:27,680
Thank you for the photo.

611
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:29,830
I don't need it anymore.

612
00:27:31,310 --> 00:27:32,790
I do want to

613
00:27:33,310 --> 00:27:34,310
start over with Xiu.

614
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:36,750
Do you really think

615
00:27:37,270 --> 00:27:38,720
you can forget everything

616
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:40,480
and act like nothing happened?

617
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:41,880
Never bringing it up again,

618
00:27:42,310 --> 00:27:43,350
and just live normally?

619
00:27:44,310 --> 00:27:45,400
I've asked myself that

620
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:47,350
over and over.

621
00:27:49,240 --> 00:27:51,240
Honestly, I don't know whether I can.

622
00:27:54,550 --> 00:27:55,480
Do you know

623
00:27:56,830 --> 00:27:58,590
when it hurts me the most?

624
00:28:00,030 --> 00:28:01,310
When you found out he cheated?

625
00:28:02,310 --> 00:28:04,070
That hurts.

626
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,030
But what hurts me the most

627
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:08,750
was after I knew,

628
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,750
Xiu lied to my face

629
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:12,830
and I couldn't expose him.

630
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:16,000
Because I realized

631
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,240
I couldn't live without him.

632
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:24,790
All I wanted

633
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:27,720
was to ask him why.

634
00:28:28,310 --> 00:28:29,160
Did he still love me?

635
00:28:30,590 --> 00:28:31,750
Isn't that pathetic?

636
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:35,110
But I love him.

637
00:28:36,510 --> 00:28:37,350
What could I do?

638
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:42,110
The scar is still there.

639
00:28:43,510 --> 00:28:44,680
If there's someone

640
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:47,640
who can make me happy again,

641
00:28:48,830 --> 00:28:49,880
why can't it

642
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:52,510
be him?

643
00:28:54,680 --> 00:28:55,750
It can be.

644
00:28:56,830 --> 00:28:58,310
But only if it's worth it.

645
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:02,400
Do you believe

646
00:29:03,350 --> 00:29:04,830
they've broken up for good?

647
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:14,740
♪At night, I wonder if it will go away♪

648
00:29:15,510 --> 00:29:16,350
No idea.

649
00:29:16,350 --> 00:29:22,220
♪At dawn, I wonder if I will be okay♪

650
00:29:22,270 --> 00:29:23,110
If…

651
00:29:26,270 --> 00:29:28,400
If I find out they're not over,

652
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,240
I'll walk away.

653
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:34,630
♪Thinking about how to stay the same♪

654
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:36,200
When the day comes,

655
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:38,640
remind me to cut my losses.

656
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:45,460
♪I lie awake♪

657
00:29:45,590 --> 00:29:47,880
(Yu should never see it.)

658
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:49,310
(It'll crush her.)

659
00:29:51,320 --> 00:29:55,080
♪Only to lie and lie awake♪

660
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:56,510
There's this play tonight.

661
00:29:58,350 --> 00:29:59,510
I think you'd like it.

662
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:05,750
(Tonight? It might not work.)

663
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:07,030
(I promised someone)

664
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:08,590
(I'd help fix a demo tonight.)

665
00:30:08,590 --> 00:30:09,960
(I need to work on it.)

666
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:12,460
(Play: Delusion Girl)

667
00:30:12,460 --> 00:30:15,460
(Written by: Luanluan)

668
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:21,160
Wrong place.

669
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:22,240
Come on.

670
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:24,160
Bro,

671
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:25,960
I bought a car.

672
00:30:26,590 --> 00:30:27,680
800,000 yuan.

673
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:29,410
Picking it up the day after tomorrow.

674
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:30,550
Showing off here, huh?

675
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:32,110
No, that's not what I meant.

676
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:37,400
Wanna play a round of Game for Peace?

677
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:49,200
Hurry, hurry.

678
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:50,400
Go. Wait a sec.

679
00:30:50,750 --> 00:30:52,240
Hurry, thirty seconds left!

680
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:53,560
On it. On it.

681
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:55,040
Heal up. Heal up.

682
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:55,920
Okay.

683
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:56,960
I'm out of meds.

684
00:30:57,640 --> 00:30:58,720
- I'll drop you one.
- Okay.

685
00:30:59,550 --> 00:31:00,440
Well,

686
00:31:01,640 --> 00:31:02,830
why did Yu marry me?

687
00:31:03,410 --> 00:31:04,270
What's wrong?

688
00:31:04,270 --> 00:31:05,550
Suddenly feel not good enough?

689
00:31:05,830 --> 00:31:06,670
Come on.

690
00:31:07,110 --> 00:31:08,200
I'm serious.

691
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:10,350
Definitely not for your money.

692
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:13,790
Then maybe your looks.

693
00:31:15,830 --> 00:31:16,790
You mocking me?

694
00:31:16,790 --> 00:31:18,510
I'm just being honest.

695
00:31:19,310 --> 00:31:21,480
You were good-looking back then.

696
00:31:21,790 --> 00:31:23,550
Guitar on your back like you owned the world.

697
00:31:23,550 --> 00:31:24,590
Looking all goofy:

698
00:31:25,030 --> 00:31:27,000
"I'm gonna make my own music!"

699
00:31:28,310 --> 00:31:29,680
That posture

700
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:30,920
bluffed everyone.

701
00:31:32,110 --> 00:31:32,950
Hey.

702
00:31:34,830 --> 00:31:35,720
I heard men mature

703
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:37,470
after they become fathers.

704
00:31:37,470 --> 00:31:38,330
Is that true?

705
00:31:38,330 --> 00:31:39,210
Is Yu pregnant?

706
00:31:39,210 --> 00:31:41,110
No, I was just asking.

707
00:31:41,110 --> 00:31:42,480
What happens when you have a kid?

708
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:45,350
Your career's finally picking up.

709
00:31:45,350 --> 00:31:46,680
Why are you looking for trouble?

710
00:31:47,110 --> 00:31:49,270
Do you feel your life needs more drama,

711
00:31:49,270 --> 00:31:50,510
Hamlet?

712
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:51,720
First marriage,

713
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:53,590
now "deadbeat dad" mode?

714
00:31:53,590 --> 00:31:55,720
Why the sudden baby fever?

715
00:31:56,340 --> 00:31:59,150
Your world is crowded enough.

716
00:31:59,350 --> 00:32:01,030
You can barely handle it.

717
00:32:01,030 --> 00:32:02,830
Like you even have a sense of responsibility.

718
00:32:02,830 --> 00:32:03,830
What are you thinking?

719
00:32:04,830 --> 00:32:05,720
Here's a question.

720
00:32:06,790 --> 00:32:07,880
Say…

721
00:32:08,860 --> 00:32:09,720
Jiang Yifan.

722
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:10,960
Yeah, Jiang Yifan.

723
00:32:10,960 --> 00:32:12,880
If... if she wants to marry you,

724
00:32:13,070 --> 00:32:14,310
and you don't want to, but she'll

725
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:15,880
marry someone else. Would you do it?

726
00:32:16,030 --> 00:32:17,240
Why bring her up?

727
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:18,440
She's your true love. Answer it.

728
00:32:23,350 --> 00:32:24,350
Get married?

729
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:28,640
Give me a break.

730
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:30,070
Marrying her is even more impossible.

731
00:32:31,680 --> 00:32:32,550
Forget it.

732
00:32:32,550 --> 00:32:33,550
You don't get it.

733
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:35,440
Having a kid might not be bad.

734
00:32:36,070 --> 00:32:37,200
He could play games with me.

735
00:32:40,830 --> 00:32:42,270
Did you forget someone?

736
00:32:43,750 --> 00:32:44,590
What about Luanluan?

737
00:32:45,310 --> 00:32:46,150
We broke up.

738
00:32:46,440 --> 00:32:47,550
I ended it today.

739
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:48,830
Knowing what a

740
00:32:48,830 --> 00:32:49,790
shameless jerk you are,

741
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,270
I need to ask you this.

742
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:52,830
After the breakup,

743
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:53,800
what are you two?

744
00:32:54,590 --> 00:32:55,430
Just friends?

745
00:32:56,510 --> 00:32:58,350
Ha, I knew it!

746
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,590
Still songwriting partners?

747
00:33:00,590 --> 00:33:02,160
You compose. She writes.

748
00:33:02,310 --> 00:33:04,200
Perfect duo, huh?

749
00:33:05,550 --> 00:33:07,590
You really are shameless,

750
00:33:07,750 --> 00:33:08,720
and sleazy.

751
00:33:12,230 --> 00:33:13,110
Alright.

752
00:33:13,110 --> 00:33:14,510
Hang in there. I'll be there soon.

753
00:33:14,790 --> 00:33:15,890
Okay. Good.

754
00:33:15,890 --> 00:33:16,750
Wine's in the trunk.

755
00:33:16,750 --> 00:33:18,110
Yes, you go ahead.

756
00:33:18,110 --> 00:33:19,110
Okay, bye.

757
00:33:19,110 --> 00:33:20,450
Sure, bye.

758
00:33:20,510 --> 00:33:21,490
- Luanluan.
- Dad.

759
00:33:22,350 --> 00:33:23,350
Break a leg!

760
00:33:23,590 --> 00:33:24,510
Thanks.

761
00:33:24,510 --> 00:33:25,640
I thought you weren't coming.

762
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:27,640
It's your directorial and writing debut.

763
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:28,590
How could miss it?

764
00:33:28,750 --> 00:33:29,960
You've missed a few before.

765
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:33,480
Yes, Director Zhao.

766
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:34,680
You're there? Okay.

767
00:33:34,690 --> 00:33:35,590
I'll be right over.

768
00:33:35,590 --> 00:33:36,880
Yes, Mr. Wang is there.

769
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:37,830
Sure, you go ahead.

770
00:33:38,640 --> 00:33:40,510
Right, let him warm you up

771
00:33:40,510 --> 00:33:41,640
to the project details.

772
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:42,920
Alright, I'll be there soon.

773
00:33:43,270 --> 00:33:44,160
Okay, got it.

774
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:45,000
No problem.

775
00:33:46,180 --> 00:33:47,030
Oh, right.

776
00:33:47,030 --> 00:33:49,030
How's it going with that married guy?

777
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:50,240
Broke up yet?

778
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:51,960
We're in love. No way we can break up.

779
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:54,160
What can you do? Can he get divorced?

780
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:55,310
He's not you.

781
00:33:58,310 --> 00:33:59,680
Your mom and I weren't meant to be.

782
00:33:59,680 --> 00:34:02,000
We fought every day.
How can we live like that?

783
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:03,110
That's not the same.

784
00:34:03,550 --> 00:34:05,030
You were only five years old.

785
00:34:05,030 --> 00:34:06,440
What could you understand?

786
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:07,310
Four, actually.

787
00:34:08,110 --> 00:34:09,510
I meant in nominal age.

788
00:34:09,510 --> 00:34:10,760
I meant in nominal age too.

789
00:34:14,550 --> 00:34:15,630
Look, you mom and I

790
00:34:15,630 --> 00:34:17,440
are doing fine apart now.

791
00:34:18,280 --> 00:34:19,150
Yeah,

792
00:34:19,150 --> 00:34:20,360
you're both doing great.

793
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:25,110
Don't be like this, okay?

794
00:34:25,110 --> 00:34:27,030
Everything I've worked so hard for

795
00:34:27,030 --> 00:34:28,440
is for you.

796
00:34:28,630 --> 00:34:29,840
Money, the company...

797
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:30,760
It will all be yours.

798
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,400
I've given you everything you wanted.

799
00:34:32,550 --> 00:34:33,840
(Delusion Girl)
You wanted to learn music.

800
00:34:33,880 --> 00:34:34,880
I found you a music teacher.

801
00:34:35,030 --> 00:34:36,070
You wanted to do theater,

802
00:34:36,070 --> 00:34:37,480
I invested in your troupe, right?

803
00:34:37,710 --> 00:34:39,000
All for your happiness.

804
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:40,400
What are you dissatisfied about?

805
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:41,680
I'm satisfied.

806
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:43,030
I just want to be in love.

807
00:34:43,030 --> 00:34:43,870
Well, at least

808
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:45,030
take it seriously, alright?

809
00:34:45,030 --> 00:34:45,920
We are serious.

810
00:34:46,110 --> 00:34:46,950
But...

811
00:34:47,670 --> 00:34:49,150
I need him, and he needs me.

812
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:52,190
Alright, fine,

813
00:34:52,190 --> 00:34:53,030
as long as you're happy,

814
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:53,930
okay?

815
00:34:55,230 --> 00:34:56,840
Oh right, after tonight's performance,

816
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:58,110
treat the troupe to dinner.

817
00:34:58,320 --> 00:35:00,280
You need to know basic social etiquette.

818
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:01,120
Got it?

819
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:03,710
- You're leaving tomorrow?
- Yeah.

820
00:35:03,710 --> 00:35:04,880
I was supposed to leave today.

821
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:07,760
Right. Yes.

822
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:08,960
Tomorrow's flight is booked.

823
00:35:09,590 --> 00:35:10,760
Booked, that's right.

824
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:12,150
Yes, that one. Go ahead and book it.

825
00:35:12,150 --> 00:35:13,960
You can just clear that through finance.

826
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:14,880
Okay, okay.

827
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:15,870
Alright, alright.

828
00:35:17,110 --> 00:35:17,960
How long?

829
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:19,400
Four months.

830
00:35:20,550 --> 00:35:21,960
Go on in, straight ahead.

831
00:35:22,230 --> 00:35:23,360
Okay.

832
00:35:23,360 --> 00:35:24,320
Call me if you need.

833
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:25,880
I'll go in then.

834
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:28,640
Hello, Director Zhao.

835
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:32,980
(Good luck!)
What would I need from you?

836
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,360
Don't forget I have a boyfriend.

837
00:35:49,320 --> 00:35:50,160
Dana.

838
00:35:50,510 --> 00:35:51,440
Yes?

839
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:52,280
Come here.

840
00:36:01,550 --> 00:36:02,510
What is it?

841
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:04,760
What's this?

842
00:36:06,550 --> 00:36:08,280
A wedding photo.

843
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:10,800
What a mess. I can't send

844
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:11,670
this to the client.

845
00:36:12,030 --> 00:36:13,880
Now you're blaming me?

846
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:16,440
When you rushed to save your little lover,

847
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:18,110
did you even think about the client?

848
00:36:19,190 --> 00:36:21,800
This shoot was supposed to be yours.

849
00:36:22,070 --> 00:36:23,710
I did my best.

850
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:30,360
I've trained you for half a year.

851
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:32,080
Even an animal could handle this.

852
00:36:32,080 --> 00:36:34,510
Don't you think I don't know why you're mad.

853
00:36:36,150 --> 00:36:37,230
Your little lover

854
00:36:37,230 --> 00:36:38,800
ran off with another guy.

855
00:36:39,110 --> 00:36:40,960
Take it out on her.

856
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,550
Why on me?

857
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:44,760
Don't bring her up.

858
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:46,280
Now you're defending her.

859
00:36:47,150 --> 00:36:49,070
If you love her so much, why not marry her?

860
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:51,360
Stop acting like some devoted lover.

861
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:52,960
You've not been at work for days.

862
00:36:54,590 --> 00:36:55,710
Want a suggestion?

863
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:57,320
Buy her a handbag

864
00:36:57,510 --> 00:36:58,550
and smooth things over.

865
00:36:58,800 --> 00:36:59,880
She's not like you.

866
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:01,600
That's right.

867
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:03,110
She's different.

